## 📊 1. Executive Summary

The global data center industry stands at a historic inflection point. Driven by **artificial intelligence (AI)**, hyperscale cloud infrastructure, and explosive edge computing growth, this sector has evolved from a niche IT infrastructure vertical into one of the world's most critical and capital-intensive industries.

<br>

### 🔢 Market Snapshot

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| 🌐 Global Market Size (2024) | **~$250 Billion+** |
| 📈 Expected Market Size (2031) | **~$500 Billion** *(doubling in ~7 years)* |
| 💰 Global Investment (2025) | **$61 Billion** *(Record High)* |
| 📡 Edge DC Market (2021) | **~$7.2 Billion** |
| 📡 Edge DC Market (2026E) | **~$19.1B – $22.2 Billion** |
| 📡 Edge Market CAGR | **~22% per annum** |
| 🏢 Equinix Revenue Forecast (2026) | **$10.1B – $10.2 Billion** |
| 🏢 Equinix EBITDA Margin Target | **50%+** |
| 🖥️ HPE Vendor Market Share | **~16%** *(Infrastructure)* |

<br>

### 💡 Key Financial Insights at a Glance

```
CapEx Range        →  $7M – $12M per MW
Power Cost (OpEx)  →  40 – 60% of total annual OpEx
EBITDA Margins     →  45 – 55% (stabilized, industry leaders)
Typical IRR        →  12 – 18% unlevered
Payback Period     →  8 – 12 years (retail colocation)
PUE Benchmark      →  1.2 – 1.5  |  Best-in-class: 1.1 – 1.2
```

