## 🏭 2. Industry Overview (2020–2026)

### 2.1 Market Size Evolution

The COVID-19 pandemic acted as an unexpected accelerant — permanently elevating baseline demand for compute and storage infrastructure by pushing enterprises toward remote work and cloud-first operations almost overnight.

| Year | Market Size | YoY Growth | Key Driver |
|------|-------------|-----------|------------|
| 2020 | ~$187B | ~8% | Remote work surge, cloud migration |
| 2021 | ~$200B | ~7% | Hyperscale build-out, edge emergence ($7.2B) |
| 2022 | ~$215B | ~7.5% | Digital transformation, AI early stage |
| 2023 | ~$230B | ~7% | GenAI demand spike, GPU cluster investments |
| 2024 | ~$250B | ~8.7% | Hyperscale leasing records, $61B global investment |
| 2025 | ~$275B | ~10% | AI infrastructure supercycle, edge ~$19.1B |
| **2026E** | **~$300B+** | **~9–11%** | **AI/cloud expansion, edge ~$22.2B** |

<br>

### 2.2 CAGR Analysis

| Segment | CAGR (2020–2026) | Notes |
|---------|-----------------|-------|
| Overall Data Center Market | ~7 – 10% | Steady compounding growth |
| Edge Data Center Market | **~22%** | Fastest-growing sub-segment |
| AI / GPU Infrastructure | **~35–40%** | Emerging explosive segment |
| India Data Center Market | **~18 – 20%** | Highest-growth major national market |

<br>

### 2.3 Regional Analysis

<details>
<summary><strong>🇺🇸 North America — Market Leader (~45–50% global share)</strong></summary>

<br>

- Dominant global market with highest concentration of campus-scale deployments
- Key corridors: **Northern Virginia (Ashburn)**, Dallas, Phoenix, Chicago
- AI campus investment in 2024–2026 concentrated in **Texas and Arizona**
- Utility interconnection queues now extend **3–7 years** in prime markets
- Northern Virginia faces multi-year utility queue backlogs due to hyperscale demand

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>🇪🇺 Europe — Established Market (~25–30% global share)</strong></summary>

<br>

- **FLAP-D markets**: Frankfurt · London · Amsterdam · Paris · Dublin
- GDPR drives data localization requirements favouring regional deployment
- Power constraints in Amsterdam and Dublin redirecting investment to **Scandinavia** (hydroelectric + natural cooling)
- Growing investment in Southern Europe, Warsaw, and Madrid

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>🌏 Asia-Pacific — Fastest Growing Major Region</strong></summary>

<br>

- Primary hubs: **Singapore, Tokyo, Sydney, Mumbai, Jakarta**
- Singapore building moratorium (selectively relaxed) redirecting investment to **Malaysia (Johor Bahru)** and Indonesia
- Japan: significant AI-driven demand from domestic hyperscalers and enterprises
- Australia: growing as sovereign cloud market with government-mandated data residency

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>🇮🇳 India — Strategic Emerging Market (18–20% CAGR)</strong></summary>

<br>

- Primary hubs: **Mumbai · Chennai · Hyderabad · Bangalore · Delhi-NCR**
- Government enablers: BharatNet, Digital India, National Data Governance Framework
- Projected **1,700+ MW commissioned capacity** by 2026
- Key investors: Yotta (Hiranandani) · Adani · NTT · STT GDC · hyperscalers
- Fastest-growing major national market globally

</details>

