## 🧮 6. Financial Model — Formulas & Framework

### 6.1 Total Cost of Ownership (TCO)

```
TCO = CapEx + (OpEx × Years) + Maintenance + Downtime Costs

Where:
  CapEx        = All-in construction cost
  OpEx         = Annual operating cost per year
  Maintenance  = 2–3% of CapEx per year (scheduled + corrective reserve)
  Downtime     = Annual Revenue × Uptime SLA Gap × Penalty Rate
```

#### TCO Worked Example — 10 MW Colocation, 10-Year Horizon

| Component | Assumption | 10-Year Total |
|-----------|-----------|--------------|
| CapEx (Construction) | $9M/MW × 10 MW | $90,000,000 |
| Annual OpEx | $2.5M/MW/yr × 10 MW × 10 yrs | $250,000,000 |
| Maintenance Reserve | 2.5% × $90M/yr × 10 yrs | $22,500,000 |
| Downtime / Contingency | 1% OpEx × 10 yrs | $2,500,000 |
| **TOTAL TCO** | | **$365,000,000** |
| **TCO per kW** | 10 MW = 10,000 kW | **$36,500 / kW** |

---

### 6.2 Revenue Model

```
Annual Revenue = Rack Rate ($/rack/month) × No. of Racks × Utilization Rate × 12

Where:
  Rack Rate        = $800 – $2,500/rack/month (market-dependent)
  No. of Racks     = Total installed rack count
  Utilization Rate = Target 80–90% at stabilization
```

#### Revenue Scenarios — 10 MW Colo (3,000 Racks, 3.3 kW avg)

| Scenario | Rack Rate | Utilization | Racks Utilized | Annual Revenue |
|----------|-----------|------------|---------------|---------------|
| Conservative | $1,200/rack/mo | 70% | 2,100 | $30,240,000 |
| **Base Case** | **$1,200/rack/mo** | **80%** | **2,400** | **$34,560,000** |
| Optimistic | $1,400/rack/mo | 90% | 2,700 | $45,360,000 |

---

### 6.3 EBITDA & IRR

```
EBITDA        = Revenue – OpEx  (excl. D&A, Interest, Tax)
EBITDA Margin = EBITDA ÷ Revenue × 100%

NPV = Σ [ Cash Flow_t / (1 + r)^t ] – Initial Investment
IRR = r  where  NPV = 0
```

```
Typical IRR:   12–18% unlevered  |  16–24% levered
Payback:       CapEx ÷ Annual Net Cash Flow
```

#### Profitability Bridge — 10 MW Colo, Base Case

| P&L Line | Annual ($M) | % Revenue |
|----------|------------|----------|
| Revenue | $34.56M | 100% |
| Less: Power Cost | –$15.55M | 45% |
| Less: Staffing | –$4.15M | 12% |
| Less: Network & Connectivity | –$2.76M | 8% |
| Less: Maintenance | –$1.73M | 5% |
| Less: G&A & Insurance | –$1.73M | 5% |
| **EBITDA (Year 1–2)** | **$8.64M** | **25%** |
| Less: D&A (CapEx / 20 yrs) | –$4.50M | 13% |
| **EBIT** | **$4.14M** | **12%** |
| *Stabilized EBITDA (Year 5+, 85%+ util.)* | *~$15–18M* | *~45–52%* |

> **Note:** Year 1–2 EBITDA is suppressed by ramp-up. Stabilized margins of **45–55%** are achieved at 85%+ utilization — typically by Year 4–5 of operations.

